config.description: Config for the module. For the resident module, its config value is defined at this level. For the inherited module, its config value is inherited from the ancestor module.

display_name.description: The human readable name to be displayed for the module.

enablement_state.description: The state of enablement for the module at the given level of the hierarchy. Possible values: ["ENABLED", "DISABLED"]

last_editor.description: The editor that last updated the custom module

location.description: Location ID of the parent organization. Only global is supported at the moment.

name.description: The resource name of the Event Threat Detection custom module. Its format is "organizations/{organization}/locations/{location}/eventThreatDetectionCustomModules/{eventThreatDetectionCustomModule}".

organization.description: Numerical ID of the parent organization.

type.description: Immutable. Type for the module. e.g. CONFIGURABLE_BAD_IP.

update_time.description: The time at which the custom module was last updated. A timestamp in RFC3339 UTC "Zulu" format, with nanosecond resolution and up to nine fractional digits. Examples: "2014-10-02T15:01:23Z" and "2014-10-02T15:01:23.045123456Z".
